<ns7270:section xmlns:ns7270="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.lang.buildingProjects.levelsOfTesting">
    
    <ns7271:title xmlns:ns7271="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Levels of Testing</ns7271:title>
<ns7272:para xmlns:ns7272="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
One should test at all levels of the software specification hierarchy. This facilitates
confidence in that the system is working correctly and enables one to localize problems
quickly. One generally differentiates between
<ns7273:itemizedlist xmlns:ns7273="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns7274:listitem xmlns:ns7274="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7275:formalpara xmlns:ns7275="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7276:title xmlns:ns7276="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Unit testing</ns7276:title><ns7277:para xmlns:ns7277="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> Each unit or class of the system is tested to verify that the 
                      detailed design for that unit has been correctly implemented.</ns7277:para> </ns7275:formalpara></ns7274:listitem>
  <ns7278:listitem xmlns:ns7278="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7279:formalpara xmlns:ns7279="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7280:title xmlns:ns7280="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Integration testing</ns7280:title><ns7281:para xmlns:ns7281="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> Progressivle larger groups of tested software components 
                             collaborating to perform progressively larger and more 
                             responsible tasks. </ns7281:para></ns7279:formalpara></ns7278:listitem>
  <ns7282:listitem xmlns:ns7282="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7283:formalpara xmlns:ns7283="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns7284:title xmlns:ns7284="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">System testing</ns7284:title><ns7285:para xmlns:ns7285="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> The system is tested in its deployment environment or a simulation
                        thereof for the complete system specifications. A variation of a
                        system test is the <ns7286:emphasis xmlns:ns7286="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">acceptance test</ns7286:emphasis> performed by the client
                        when deciding whether or not to accept the delivered version of
                        the system.</ns7285:para></ns7283:formalpara></ns7282:listitem>
</ns7273:itemizedlist></ns7272:para>

<ns7287:para xmlns:ns7287="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Of course, to be able to write tests one has to have detailed system specifications. 
Often the detailed system specifications can be supplied in the form of the test itself.
In this course we shall focus on unit or class testing.</ns7287:para>
    
